Test looks good - there is a typo in the commit message (Telemtry) if that matters.
Before starting creating any report delete all existing reports.
I believe one ${HTTP_OK} is required here
why two status code for success and failure? One should be good enough
What about the fail status? One should be good enough there also.
not really required because it gets tested by other test cases already.
remove this change id. Its coming two times

End with the period. Also only keep first character as upper case like below.


    [Documentation]  Verify error while creating telemetry report more than max report limit.
This code and line 76 code is same. Better to have a separate keyword to delete all telemetry report. later youhave call that keyword in setup and teardown of this test case.
This is not making change. Can we have something more meaningful?

End with period. Also change the description something like below.

    # report_name      Name of telemetry report which needs to be created.

Keep expected_result instead of result and change the description like below. 

    # expected_result        Expected result of report creation.
keep the argument name as expected_result which make much sense
remove white spaces in all place of this code
# property    Name of MetrixDefination's property for report. E.g. Ambient_0_Temp.
no blank line required between twi argument description.
I guess HTTP_OK is also required here. Please cross check

Can we keep it as metric_definition_name instead on metrix and change the description to some thing like below.

```
    # Description of argument(s):
    # metric_definition_name        Name of metric definition like Ambient_0_Temp.
    
```
I am unable to make out why this get is required. Please add example for this response.
expected_result variable created but unused in the keyword.
Looks like success/fail are only options for expected_result so please do mention it in the description.
